This is by no means an exhaustive tutorial on best practices.  It is, simply put, a tutorial of how you might authenticate a user using MongoDB as your Pylons's Model.


This file is for you to describe the userdemo application. Typically
you would include information such as the information below:

Installation and Setup
======================

Install ``userdemo`` using easy_install::

    easy_install userdemo

Make a config file as follows::

    paster make-config userdemo config.ini

Tweak the config file as appropriate and then setup the application::

    paster setup-app config.ini

Then you are ready to go.
